      "content": "exactly. and it feels like when people try to defend it, they just call anyone who disagrees \"bigoted\" or \"problematic\" to shut down the conversation. if the goal is supposed to be \"justice\" and \"inclusion,\" but the method is just silencing anyone with a different view, isn't the whole movement inherently flawed? shouldn't we admit that the censorship aspect is the real issue here?",
